book author, you figure, well,

00:38:01.650 --> 00:38:04.240
this will be coming out in a year
or two, and I won't care about it.

00:38:04.240 --> 00:38:05.660
Do you think that's true or not?

00:38:05.660 --> 00:38:07.660
&gt;&gt; Bob Woodward: I think
no, it's somewhat true,

00:38:07.660 --> 00:38:11.220
and they realize you're talking

00:38:11.220 --> 00:38:15.050
to other people, and
it, it gets around.

00:38:15.050 --> 00:38:19.150
I mean, even the Obama White House,
I've done two books on Obama,

00:38:19.150 --> 00:38:21.990
and people would say,
okay, he's working on this,

00:38:21.990 --> 00:38:25.840
he's got these memos or
documents, or the accounts

00:38:25.840 --> 00:38:27.790
of what happened at meetings.

00:38:27.790 --> 00:38:30.320
&gt;&gt; David M. Rubenstein: But
the, do you ever say to people,

00:38:30.320 --> 00:38:33.170
