we could've done a better job,

00:55:22.390 --> 00:55:26.880
and he said, to his credit, he
said, okay, we need to make sure

00:55:26.880 --> 00:55:32.190
that we provide in the
Washington Post as much background

00:55:32.190 --> 00:55:38.700
on who these people really are,
and then he said the goal is

00:55:38.700 --> 00:55:42.760
that no one can go to the polls in
November and say, I couldn't find

00:55:42.760 --> 00:55:45.250
out who the final candidates were.

00:55:45.250 --> 00:55:51.030
And that's exactly the right goal,
and he said to me, you tell Marty,

00:55:51.030 --> 00:55:56.270 position:56%
Marty Baron, the Editor of the Post,
this was Bezos, like a good CEO,

00:55:56.270 --> 00:56:00.340
was totally breaking the chain of
command, and said pass on to Marty,

00:56:00.340 --> 00:56:03.320
he will have the resources
to do this.

00:56:03.320 --> 00:56:07.300
And if you talk to Marty Baron,
he'd say Bezos has delivered.

00:56:07.300 --> 00:56:12.410
We have many people, we have
40 people covering the national

00:56:12.410 --> 00:56:16.430
campaign one way or another, it's
more than the New York Times,

00:56:16.430 --> 00:56:20.130
and we have had some
fabulous stories.

00:56:20.130 --> 00:56:22.960
We've done a book on Trump.

00:56:22.960 --> 00:56:25.440
Now, are people going
to get up and applaud?

00:56:25.440 --> 00:56:27.930 position:56%
No. I mean, we still are distrusted.

00:56:27.930 --> 00:56:34.250
We're still on probation, and
we need to figure out how to get

00:56:34.250 --> 00:56:38.760
out of probation, that is the
monstrous problem we've got

00:56:38.760 --> 00:56:40.060
to confront.

00:56:40.060 --> 00:56:41.510 position:56%
